### RustDesk Server (HBBS) - Modifications
License: GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (inherited from original)
Copyright: 2026 BetterDesk Console Contributors
Location: hbbs-patch/ directory

Modified files in RustDesk Server:
- src/database.rs: Added is_device_banned() method with rusqlite integration
- src/peer.rs: Added ban checks in update_pk(), get(), and get_id_by_addr() method
- src/rendezvous_server.rs: Added ban enforcement in RequestRelay and PunchHoleRequest
- Cargo.toml: Added rusqlite = "0.27" dependency

Build system:
- build.sh: Automated patch application and compilation script

Modifications implement:
- Bidirectional ban enforcement (blocks connections FROM and TO banned devices)
- Synchronous database queries using rusqlite to avoid Tokio runtime conflicts
- Memory-based device tracking via get_id_by_addr() for initiator identification
- Comprehensive logging of ban enforcement actions

Source availability:
All modifications are available in the hbbs-patch/ directory and must be
provided to any user accessing the modified server over a network, as
required by AGPL-3.0 Section 13.

Original RustDesk source: https://github.com/rustdesk/rustdesk-server
Modified version source: This repository (hbbs-patch/ directory)

